<SLUG> BC-FBC-MOTOR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CANSECO SOUNDING UPBEAT ABOUT FUTURE WITH RANGERS
</HEADLINE>
 CITY BOWL CAPSULE-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By WENDELL BARNHOUSE 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Louisville (7-4) vs. Marshall (11-1) Time: 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Location: Silverdome, Pontiac, Mich.
</P>
<P>
   TV: ESPN2.
</P>
<P>
   How they got here: Marshall won the Mid-American Conference
championship and earned the MAC's bid to this bowl. Louisville is
filling the at-large berth.
</P>
<P>
   Retrospective: Marshall, which has been a I-A school for just
two seasons, is making its second bowl appearance. The Thundering
Herd lost to Mississippi in last year's Motor City Bowl. Louisville
is making its sixth bowl appearance and its first since the 1993
Liberty. The Cardinals are 3-1-1.
</P>
<P>
   Opponents: The teams played no common opponents. Opponents'
combined won-loss records _ Marshall, 53-68; Louisville, 55-54.
</P>
<P>
   What you need to know: This bowl should come with its own air
raid warning. Louisville's Chris Redman ranks 12th in pass
efficiency and passed for 4,042 yards and 29 touchdowns; Marshall's
Chad Pennington is 18th in pass efficiency and passed for 3,419
yards and 24 TDs. The quarterback with the best game will find his
name on next season's list of Heisman Trophy candidates.
</P>
<P>
   Keep an eye on: For Louisville _ QB Chris Redman, TE Ibn Green,
RB LeRoy Collins. For Marshall _ QB Chad Pennington, RB Doug
Chapman, DB Daninelle Derricott.
</P>
<P>
   Louisville update: The Cardinals were 1-10 last season, but
first-year coach John L. Smith came from Utah State and produced a
winning season. Louisville ranks 105th in pass defense. It allowed
242 yards per game and gave up 26 scoring passes. Louisville opened
the season by losing to Kentucky and Utah.
</P>
<P>
   Marshall update: The Thundering Herd, despite the loss of wide
receiver Randy Moss, has continued to win. Last season with Moss,
Marshall was 10-3. Marshall is 14th nationally in pass defense and
23rd in total defense. The Thundering Herd's only loss came at
Bowling Green.
</P>
<P>
   Louisville wins if: Its pass defense can find a way to slow down
Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   Marshall wins if: Its pass defense can find a way to slow down
Redman.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
