<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES_NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TVERDOVSKY NOT STEAMED OVER LACK OF HOT WATER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT _ Coyotes defenseman Oleg Tverdovsky overheard a media
member complaining on the team bus on the way to Tuesday morning's
skate and again in the hotel elevator after the skate.
</P>
<P>
   ``Are you guys still talking about that?'' he quizzed. ``You're
nothing but a bunch of whiners.''
</P>
<P>
   He could have included several of his teammates on that list,
including Keith Tkachuk.
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes' abode here is the plush Atheneum Suites in Greek
Town. But with temperatures outside dropping to 7 degrees, several
rooms were without heat and all the rooms were devoid of hot water
Tuesday morning, robbing everyone of a shower unless he wanted to
brave tap water that was not far away from being slush.
</P>
<P>
   ``You guys should have been with me when I was kid in Russia,''
Tverdovsky said. ``Me and a friend of mine were sent to the Sports
Academy, and when we checked into the room where we stayed, there
were two windows but no glass in them. There was snow inside the
room and on one of the beds.
</P>
<P>
   ``And we didn't have hot water to shower with for the whole year
. . . no kidding, for the whole year.''
</P>
<P>
   OK, so maybe North Americans are somewhat spoiled. &QL;  &QL; 
Watchful eye &QL;  &QL; 
Coach Jim Schoenfeld plans to keep a watchful eye on his two
veteran second-line forwards Greg Adams, 35, and Rick Tocchet, 34,
to ensure they get enough rest as the season progresses.
</P>
<P>
   Adams in particular seemed to show the effects of playing three
games in four nights during the recent four-game trip that ended in
St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're looking at things right now for Gus (Adams) and Tocchet
where their practice time will be limited at times,'' Schoenfeld
said. ``For instance, if we have a 40- to 50-minute practice, they
might go off after 20 minutes at times. Have them do just enough to
take some shots at the goaltender and to get a good warm-up.
</P>
<P>
   ``We finally gave him a couple days rest after St. Louis, and
Gus had great legs against the Islanders. You have to recognize
what you have and don't go to the well too many times. Just like
you can't rush young guys along too fast, your older guys aren't
going to get younger.''
</P>
<P>
   Adams supplied two assists and Tocchet added another in the
lopsided victory over the Red Wings Tuesday night. &QL;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
