<HEADER>
A3717 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-KIDS-ON-VIDS24-COX     12-23 1128
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS-ON-VIDS24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Children's videos get thumbs-up from kids, grownups
 &HT;    By Meredith Moss
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ We invited kids, parents and teachers to review a
batch of current children's videos.
</P>
<P>
   Here are some we all liked and can recommend. Prices vary, but
most cost between $10 and $20, depending on length:
</P>
<P>
   Preschool and toddlers
</P>
<P>
   _ The group of 3- and 4 year-olds who watched The Bear were
mesmerized. The charming adventures of a little girl and a huge
polar bear celebrate friendship and love. It's based on the book by
Raymond Briggs and produced by the creators of The Snowman, another
Briggs winner. ``I liked it because everybody got home safe,'' said
one 4-year-old video critic (Buena Vista Home Video).
</P>
<P>
   _ Most of the kids ages 2 to 4 watching Sing &AMP; Dance With Barney
couldn't sit still, and that's the way it should be. They were busy
clapping, moving and singing. The soon-to-be released video
celebrates Barney's 10 years and features reunion appearances by
Kathy, Michael, Tosha, Min and Jason. Teachers say kids begin to
find the purple dinosaur ``babyish'' after the age of 5, but little
ones still like him a lot. This video won't be out until
mid-January, but there are other Barney tapes _ such as the Barney
Safety Video _ if you need one in time for Christmas (Lyrick
Studio).
</P>
<P>
   _ Mention Blue's Clues and toddlers light up. The Nickelodeon
hit leads kids from paw print to paw print as host Steve and his
dog Blue help kids learn to reason. These two videos encourage
interaction and are definite hits with toddlers and preschoolers:
Blue's Clues Story Time and Blue's Clues Arts &AMP; Crafts (Paramount).
</P>
<P>
   _ Little ones adore seeing their favorite costumed characters,
and that's one of the reasons Disney's Sing Along Songs videos are
so popular. In The Twelve Days of Christmas, Mickey, Minnie,
Donald, Goofy and their friends enjoy a sleigh ride through the
wintry woods and a country yuletide hoe-down. Words are flashed on
the screen so kids can sing along.
</P>
<P>
   Elementary school
</P>
<P>
   _ Many kids are interested in flight and space. Follow up their
interest with videos on the subject. Two of the best are The Big
Space Shuttle and The Big Plane Trip, which allow kids to learn
about the space program and blast off with the astronauts, learn
how airplanes work and fly with the pilots in the cockpit (Little
Mammoth Media). Another interesting airplane video is Fred Levine's
Cleared for Takeoff, which follows a family from beginning to end
of a trip and takes viewers behind the scenes at an airport (Fred
Levine Productions).
</P>
<P>
   _ Videos can be used to help ignite a child's interest in
reading or _ for kids who already love books _ bring favorite
characters to life.
</P>
<P>
   One example is Madeline , the Ludwig Bemelman classic series
about a Parisian girl and her schoolmates. There's the new
live-action film with Frances McDormand as Miss Clavel (Columbia
Tri-Star) and a series of animated videos from Golden aimed at kids
between 4 and 8. Check out Madeline &AMP; The New House, Madeline at
Cooking School and others.
</P>
<P>
   Another example is Winnie the Pooh. If you're looking for a
holiday video, consider Winnie the Pooh and Christmas, Too. The
originals are still great: A Blustery Day and The Honey Tree
(Disney).
</P>
<P>
   _ For kids who love science, the ``Eyewitness'' videos are based
on the fascinating book series and include titles ranging from
Monster and Flight to Bear and Volcano (DK Vision). Other
possibilities: Disney's ``Amazing Animal'' series with titles such
as An Animal Year and Bill Nye the Science Guy Videos for kids 8
and older (Disney).
</P>
<P>
   _ Young folks with an artistic bent will be fascinated by the
``Notes Alive'' videos from the Minnesota Orchestra. The most
recent, The Nutcracker , interweaves footage of the orchestra, a
ballet performance and animation of Maurice Sendak illustrations.
First in the excellent series was On the Day You Were Born, a
similar format with an animated version of the Debra Frasier
picturebook.
</P>
<P>
   _ Parents and grandparents looking for a bit of holiday
nostalgia will like sharing the series of ``Golden Oldies'' with
their kids. Danny and Marlo Thomas star in Cricket on the Hearth ,
plus restored versions of the original Frosty the Snowman, Rudolph
the Red-Nosed Reindeer and The Little Drummer Boy.
</P>
<P>
   Family films
</P>
<P>
   _ You won't be surprised to hear that the older kids who watched
the full-length feature films gave top ratings to movies such as
The Parent Trap, Air Bud: Golden Retriever, Dr. Dolittle and
Simba's Pride.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought Dr. Dolittle had a lot of action and was really
funny,'' said Jacob Levitt, 8.
</P>
<P>
   Brian Horwitz said The Parent Trap was ``probably the best movie
I've seen in my whole life.''
</P>
<P>
   His mom preferred Disney's Summer of the Monkeys , a
coming-of-age adventure about a 12-year-old farm boy who makes
friends with four runaway circus monkeys.
</P>
<P>
   I objected to the language in Dr. Dolittle and found Simba's
Pride unnecessarily violent and scary for young children.
</P>
<P>
   Kids and adults of every age _ except little ones _ are likely
to love The Parent Trap.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where do Christmas trees come from? The Christmas Tree Story
is a fascinating look at them _ from seedling to recycling
(Earthwalker Entertainment).
</P>
<P>
   _ I Love Christmas and Toy Trains &AMP; Christmas 2 (TM Books &AMP;
Videos) are entertaining for families who love watching electric
trains go round and round. Tom McComas combines Christmas music and
stories with smoke-puffing Lionel train layouts. These are great
videos for dads who always wanted a toy train of their own and
never got one, and for collectors. Younger train addicts will like
videos featuring Thomas the Tank Engine &AMP; Friends.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't neglect the classics, the full-length features that you
can all watch again and again. We're talking Mary Poppins, Mary
Martin's Peter Pan, Babe, Mrs. Doubtfire and Lady &AMP; the Tramp . One
of my favorites is Fly Away Home , the true story of a flock of
geese that lose their mother and are helped by 13-year-old Amy and
her dad (Columbia Tri-Star).
</P>
<P>
   _ Looking for a perfect video for Christmas Eve or Christmas
Day?
</P>
<P>
   A Hollywood Christmas brings together well-known scenes from
more than 40 years of Christmas films. Hosted by Jane Seymour, the
journey begins with the first Santa Claus film in 1898 and includes
clips from Home Alone, A Christmas Story , Miracle on 34th Street,
A Christmas Carol and others (Real Entertainment). A similar video,
TV Guide Looks at Christmas , includes holiday clips from popular
television shows.
</P>
<P>
   Meredith Moss writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
