A3734 &Cx1f; tad-z
u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SIMPLE24-COX     12-23 0387
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SIMPLE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    It's simple: Wild rice offering fills the holiday bill
 &HT;    By Ann Heller
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Like most of you, I'm working today. I'll be
lucky to sneak away at midday, with just enough time to get a head
start on Christmas Eve dinner.
</P>
<P>
   Friends from out of town will arrive about 6 p.m. for our ritual
celebration, which this year will be a seafood feast. There's not
much time to think about even the small dinner planned for
Christmas Day.
</P>
<P>
   But because the holiday is a pull-out-the-stops day for
ingredients, wild rice is always on the dinner menu. My favorite
recipe is this one for Wild Wild Rice, which adds the intense
flavors of dried mushrooms and pecans to the rice.
</P>
<P>
   It's an old recipe from my ``It's Simple'' column, which has
been on vacation.
</P>
<P>
   WILD WILD RICE
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings
</P>
<P>
   1 ounce dried shiitake mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   1 cup wild rice
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons chopped toasted pecans
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoons butter
</P>
<P>
   freshly grated nutmeg
</P>
<P>
   Soak the mushrooms in 1 cup warm water for 30 minutes. Strain
the mushrooms, reserving the liquid, and rinse the mushrooms under
cold water to remove any grit. Chop the mushrooms, discarding any
hard stems, and set aside.
</P>
<P>
   Rinse the rice under cold water until the water runs clear (some
packages carry an advisory that the rice has been prewashed).
Drain.
</P>
<P>
   Add enough water to the reserved mushroom liquid to make 3 cups
and bring to a boil; add the rice and salt. Cover, bring back to a
boil, then reduce heat to a simmer and cook for about 45 minutes
until the water is evaporated and the rice is tender. Do not
overcook to the mushy stage.
</P>
<P>
   When the rice is done, remove from heat, cover with a paper
towel, replace lid and let stand off the heat for 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   While the rice stands, heat the butter in a small skillet and
cook the mushrooms and pecans. Just before serving, stir the pecans
and mushrooms into the wild rice and add a few gratings of nutmeg.
</P>
<P>
   Approximate nutritional analysis per serving: 238 calories, 8.5
g fat, 12 mg cholesterol, 537 mg sodium.
</P>
<P>
   Ann Heller writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
E-mail: ann_heller(AT)coxohio.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
