   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ If Clinton had lied about eating
Mexican food, would it be perjury? (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Send in Bruce Willis! Could this
be anything but the political apocalypse, the Beltway Armageddon?
Consider the omens:
</P>
<P>
   Larry Flynt as Deep Throat. Henry Hyde as the Enforcer of
Conscience. The President, already in trouble for his, er, poor
impulse control, bombs Iraq on the eve of his impeachment vote. The
news toggles back and forth between Iraq and impeachment.
Meanwhile, the President's job-approval ratings soar to a record 73
percent. Do you wonder if you died and are spending the afterlife
in a Fellini movie? (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ ``It's obvious you have never
worked in retail,'' wrote Mrs. Gail Micek of Bellevue, Neb., who
said she was writing for ``all sales associates everywhere'' who
took offense at my column. The column that upset Mrs. Micek began:
``It's amazing how many people work in retail sales but don't know
anything about the products they sell.'' (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   JEFFERSON-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ How different today's
dolls are from the one I knew as a child. I speak literally, for,
from my earliest memory, I had one doll. I played house with her,
but ours was a love-hate relationship. (Jefferson, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
