   STEPMOMS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Instant love. If there is one
big myth common to stepfamilies, it's that children and their
stepmothers or stepfathers should instantly love each other. ``Love
me, love my children. You don't need to love them to be
successful,'' says Dr. Elaine Rotenberg, a West Palm Beach family
psychologist. ``It's OK to realize that stepparents and
stepchildren may never really like each other, and they don't have
to love each other.'' But she adds: ``They can get along with each
other.'' Love takes time. And stepmothers in particular have a hard
time as heads of new families. (Susman, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
