<P>
   GOLF-CLUBS (Carlsbad, Calif.) _ Perhaps it is no coincidence
that as the cold war died down, the golf club war heated up. Club
manufacturers have turned to the space-age materials, computer
techniques and laid-off engineers of their Southern California
neighbors, the aerospace companies. And they guard their secrets
just as closely. Now, also like the aerospace business, the golf
club business is going through a retrenchment. By Andrew Pollack
and Sharon R. King.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
