   To celebrate the release of these excerpts, The New York Times
Syndicate is running a history trivia quiz based on the book. Every
day this week we are offering on the wire one question related to
the world of journalism. The first editor to fax back the correct
answer will win a copy of ``The American Century.''
</P>
<P>
   THE ANSWER TO YESTERDAY'S QUESTION: The New York Times was the
first newspaper to publish the Pentagon Papers.
</P>
<P>
   Congratulations to CAMERON TEW, Features Editor at The
Herald-Sun in Durham, N.C. A copy of ``The American Century'' is in
the mail!
</P>
