   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KING-PARADE (Houston) _ A state district judge has ruled that
the city of Houston conspired to give one of the opposing Martin
Luther King parade organizers a permit, thus keeping its rival
group from getting a permit for Jan. 18, the official Martin Luther
King holiday. The ruling means the MLK Jr. Parade Foundation cannot
conduct its parade on the Jan. 18 holiday. By ERIC HANSON.
</P>
