   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-39-AGGIES (Undated) _ The last time Texas A&AMP;M played in the
Sugar Bowl, the Aggies walked away with the national championship.
As Texas A&AMP;M heads back to New Orleans this year for the first time
in 59 years, we look back at the 1939 Aggies _ generally regarded
as the greatest team in A&AMP;M's history. By JEROME SOLOMON.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-REDSKINS (Undated) _ The Washington Redskins have rebounded
from a 0-7 start to win six of their past eight games and salvage a
respectable season. But will it be enough to save coach Norv
Turner's job? Much could depend on how the Redskins fare in this
week's regular-season finale against the Dallas Cowboys. By JODY
GOLDSTEIN.
