   SMALLBIZ-INTERNET _ Web sites may be the storefront of the
future. But are small businesses taking advantage of the online
world? Apparently not and big companies that provide such services
are looking to change that. Everybody has a computer but few small
business owners use it to their full advantage. The Internet
service providers or ISPs are beginning to realize the small
business owner is a potential cash cow. BellSouth, which has join a
string of other big companies going after the small business
market, estimates that 260,000 of its small business customers will
go online this year. Also, we ask small business and high tech
consultants: Do you advise people to have a web sites? Is a web
presence for small business necessary or is it is just smoke and
mirrors? (Joyner &AMP; Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
