<HEADLINE>
LET THE SPIRIT OF GIVING LAST ALL YEAR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   You've seen them: men crouched in the cold shadow of a downtown
skyscraper, women begging for money to buy food, children abused
and neglected.
</P>
<P>
   For most of the year, they are, maybe, somebody else's problem _
faceless individuals with no name, no address and no connection
with your life. But then the holiday season arrives, and with joy
in your heart, you determinATQ0Z ATQ0Z +++-P
</P>
