warning of a chemical threat forced the evacuation of 200 employees
at the Time Warner Cable Television Co. offices in suburban
Chatsworth, Calif., Wednesday, the third similar threat in the area
since Friday. By Phillip Browne and Steve Carney. (Will move in the
``n'' California and the ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   TICKET-THEFTS (Los Angeles) _ Beware of bargain plane tickets.
Three more travel agencies have been burglarized in Los Angeles'
San Fernando Valley, losing a handful of blank tickets. Police say
the area has been hit with a half dozen similar robberies and
burglaries, carried out by thieves who resell the tickets. By Lisa
Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``n'' California and the ``a''
national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   ROCKETDYNE-LAWSUIT (Simi Valley, Calif.) _ A federal appellate
court has denied the Boeing Co.'s appeal of class action status in
a lawsuit over contamination at Rocketdyne's Santa Susana Field
Lab, allowing the sweeping case that could involve more than
300,000 residents and property owners in the area to move forward.
By Lisa Mascaro. (Will move in the ``n'' California and the ``a''
national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LENO-KIDS (Los Angeles) _ The students at Balboa Magnet
Elementary School in suburban Northridge, Calif., are becoming
regulars on ``The Tonight Show.'' They appeared in November to put
on a Thanksgiving skit, and returned with a Christmas skit. By
Sherry Joe Crosby. (Will move in the ``n'' California and the ``a''
national news files.)
