<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Television highlights for the upcoming holiday weekend
 &HT;    By Byrone Battles
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Christmas Unwrapped'' 9 a.m. The History Channel _ Now that
you're totally exhausted from the Christmas frenzy, find out the
origins of such traditions as the Christmas tree, mistletoe, Santa
Claus, the exchanging of presents and cards, and the focus on
children and the family.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Very Merry Christmas Parade'' 10 a.m. ABC _ The two-hour
parade is filled with delightful holiday entertainment, Disney's
favorite characters and musical guests. Hosts include Caroline Rhea
and Richard Kind.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  College Football _ The game's top seniors storm the gridiron
in the Blue-Gray All-Star Classic (noon, ABC ), Oregon plays
Colorado in the Aloha Bowl in Honolulu (3:30 p.m. ABC ), and Air
Force faces Washington in the Oahu Bowl (8:30 p.m. ESPN ).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Scrooge'' (1951) Noon WATL _ A fine British version with a
sterling cast (including Alastair Sim) in the Dickens classic about
London's meanest miser.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``It's a Wonderful Life'' 8 p.m. NBC _ Get out you hankies for
the last showing this year of the ultimate Christmas movie. Frank
Capra directed this heartwarming 1946 drama starring James Stewart,
Donna Reed and Lionel Barrymore.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``On Golden Pond'' 5:30 p.m. TNT _ Oscars went to Henry Fonda,
Katharine Hepburn and writer Ernest Thompson for this heartwarming
1981 story of an elderly couple and their estranged daughter (Jane
Fonda).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Manchurian Candidate'' 6 p.m. AMC _ This riveting 1962
political thriller, with Frank Sinatra, Laurence Harvey, Janet
Leigh and Angela Lansbury, was brilliantly directed by John
Frankenheimer. A true original.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil'' 8 p.m. HBO _ Clint
Eastwood directed this 1997 adaptation of the best seller about a
high-profile murder trial in Savannah. John Cusack and Kevin Spacey
star.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``This Year in Country Music '98'' 10 p.m. TNN _ Lorianne
Crook and Charlie Chase host this hour featuring George Strait,
Faith Hill, Shania Twain and LeAnn Rimes.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Season of Joy: The Gift of Sports'' 10 a.m. Lifetime _ This
celebration of women in sports includes interviews with prominent
female athletes and a tribute to Olympic sprinter Florence
Griffith-Joyner.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Imitation of Life'' (1959) 1:45 p.m. AMC _ A tear-jerker
with Lana Turner as a fame-greedy actress who neglects her daughter
and her black friend whose daughter repudiates her heritage and
passes for white.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Indian in the Cupboard'' 7 p.m. ABC _ A tale about a boy
who receives a cupboard for his birthday and discovers when he puts
a little figurine into it that it comes to life.
</P>
<P>
   Byrone Battles writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
