transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-INDIA-UNIVERSITY-NYT (moved on Sunday, Dec. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Dec. 20,
about Allahabad University in India misstated the number of India's
universities and colleges in some copies. There are 10,000, not
1,000.
</P>
<P>
   BC-IMPEACH-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Dec. 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Dec. 22,
about the Senate's consideration of the impeachment case against
President Clinton referred incorrectly to the conduct of a trial.
The Chief Justice of the United States, not the Senate Rules
Committee, would preside.
</P>
<P>
   BC-IMPEACH-CLINTON-NYT (moved on Sunday, Dec. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Dec. 20,
about the events leading to the impeachment of President Clinton
referred incompletely to the authorship of the referral submitted
to the House of Representatives by the office of the independent
counsel. The narrative part was written by Stephen Bates and Craig
S. Lerner. The section reviewing possible grounds for impeachment
was written by Brett M. Kavanaugh, Andrew D. Leipold and Julie L.
Myers.
</P>
</TEXT>
