firefighter is taken from the scene of a fire which left four
people dead in New York's Upper Westside. The apartment was owned
by the family of Macaulay Culkin, star of ``Home Alone,'' among
other movies. The Culkin family was safe, a publicist said. The
dead, two men and two women, were found on higher floors of the
51-story building. It is believed they died of smoke inhalation.
(Angel Franco/New York Times Photo)
